defaultWhat role should the Government have in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers?
default&#xa0;
defaultFunding
default&#xa0;
defaultFollowing on from the chief medical officer’s statement that all NIHR 
defaultfunded departments should achieve Athena SWAN Silver within a reasonable time period, this should be extended to all research council funded departments.
default&#xa0;
defaultThere should be 
defaultfinancial 
defaultprovision in all publicly funded PhD and postdoc positions for the possibil
defaultity of maternity or paternity leave.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe
default assessment
default of research track-record by funding panels
default should
default take into account periods of part time
default working
default, career breaks, or parental leave.
default&#xa0;
defaultSupport and information for complainants and whistle blowers
default&#xa0;
defaultThe gov
defaulternment should provide support and information to employees for the pursuance of grievances or whistle blowing in organisations that are not operating 
defaultin line with existing equal
default opportunities policies and legislation.
default&#xa0;
defaultCommission social research
default&#xa0;
defaultThe gove
defaultrnment should commission research that measures the experience of women working in science and those who have left STEM careers
default,
default in order to establish qualitative base lines for future improvements in culture and work environment. Such research should be f
defaultree to question the rational orthodoxy and so present solutions outside of the established political and legal structures, which have so far failed to address the problem
default for more than 40 years
default.
